<div class="page-header">
	<h1>Creating Tutorials</h1>
</div>

<p>Creating new tutorials is super-simple. The tutorial itself is made up of pages. You can have as many pages as you want, and they will be automatically paginated for you.</p>
<p>Pages are represented by individual <code>.tpl</code> files, called <code>page1.tpl</code>, <code>page2.tpl</code> etc.</p>
<p>You can also have a <code>demos</code> folder, where you can put embeddable demos.</p>

<hr />

<p>So, a basic tutorial folder might look like:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Demos
		<ul>
			<li>
				Demo1
				<ul>
					<li>demo.tpl</li>
					<li>demo.js</li>
					<li>demo.css</li>
					<li>demo.html</li>
				</ul>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>page1.tpl</li>
	<li>page2.tpl</li>
	<li>page3.tpl</li>
</ul>

